# Envoy Gateway for `<project-name>` (2.0.0 candidate)

<!-- Audit: B.8.4 (b8-4-envoy-gateway, FR-B84-020) -->

This tree is the **2.0.0 target** API-gateway intent for `<project-name>`,
authored as an additive sibling alongside the frozen 1.0.0 Kong tree
(`infra/kong/`). It is Gateway-API-native (Envoy Gateway), routes to the same
`<project-name>-backend` Service that Kong targets, and removes nothing ÔÇö
canary-by-route migration per `docs/new-archetypes-plan.md` ┬ž4.1. Standard:
`.forge/standards/gateway.yaml`.

> **Status**: the `full-stack-monorepo / 2.0.0` schema is a `candidate`
> (`scaffoldable: false`). Kong remains the constitutional API gateway
> (Article VIII.1) until the B.8.14 amendment + version bump. This tree
> describes the target; it is not scaffolded by default.

## Delivery model ÔÇö hybrid (ADR-B84-003)

| Plane | What | How |
|-------|------|-----|
| **Control plane** | Envoy Gateway controller **+** the Gateway API CRDs | Upstream OCI Helm chart (Atlas-provided install ÔÇö below) |
| **Data plane** | `GatewayClass` / `Gateway` / `HTTPRoute` / `BackendTLSPolicy` | The kustomize manifests in this dir |

## Control-plane install (Atlas-provided)

The Envoy Gateway controller and the Gateway API CRDs it requires are installed
from the upstream OCI Helm chart ÔÇö this tree vendors **no** CRD or controller
copies:

```sh
helm install eg oci://docker.io/envoyproxy/gateway-helm \
  --version v1.8.0 \
  -n envoy-gateway-system --create-namespace
```

- **Chart**: `oci://docker.io/envoyproxy/gateway-helm` `--version v1.8.0`
  (pinned in `.forge/standards/gateway.yaml` `versions.envoy_gateway_chart`).
- **Gateway API CRD bundle**: `v1.5.1` (vendored by the chart; pinned in
  `gateway.yaml` `versions.gateway_api_bundle`). Ships `GatewayClass`,
  `Gateway`, `HTTPRoute`, and `BackendTLSPolicy` at GA
  `gateway.networking.k8s.io/v1`.
- **Namespace**: `envoy-gateway-system` (controller). The data-plane resources
  below deploy into the application namespace.
- **Values**: tune the chart values (replicas, resources, logging) Atlas-side;
  no values file is vendored here.

## Data-plane render

```sh
kustomize build infra/k8s/envoy-gateway

# Strict schema validation (Gateway API CRDs must be on the cluster /
# in kubeconform's schema set):
kustomize build infra/k8s/envoy-gateway | kubeconform --summary --strict
```

## Resources

| File | Kind | Role |
|------|------|------|
| `gatewayclass.yaml` | `GatewayClass` | Binds to the Envoy Gateway controller (`gateway.envoyproxy.io/gatewayclass-controller`). |
| `gateway.yaml` | `Gateway` | HTTP listener (`:80`); HTTPS/TLS listener is overlay-patchable. |
| `httproute.yaml` | `HTTPRoute` | Routes `/` Ôćĺ `<project-name>-backend:8080` (the same Service Kong targets ÔÇö additive parity). |
| `backendtlspolicy.yaml` | `BackendTLSPolicy` | Upstream TLS validation for `<project-name>-backend` (GA `v1`). |

## Coexistence with Kong (additive-first)

Both gateways converge on `<project-name>-backend` (`fsm-backend`, http port
8080). B.8.4 adds Envoy **in parallel**; it does not touch
`infra/kong/kong.yml.example.tmpl`. The route-cutover/canary mechanism is
B.8.10; Kong removal + the actual 1.0.0 Ôćĺ 2.0.0 bump is B.8.14. Transport is
Connect/gRPC-Web pass-through at the gateway (ADR-B84-006) ÔÇö any RESTÔćögRPC
transcoding decision belongs to B.8.6.
